FBIS4-27738 "dreas108_l_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 Philippines Ramos Asks Indonesia To Release Fishermen Ramos Asks Indonesia To Release Fishermen BK0306134194 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 3 Jun 94 BK0306134194 Quezon City Radio Filipinas English BFN [Text] For its strong effort to stave off the holding of the Asia-Pacific Conference on East Timor in Manila, the Ramos administration is asking Indonesia to return the gesture. President Ramos is asking for the immediate release of some 90 Filipino fishermen detained since last month in North Sulawesi. President Ramos expressed hope that Jakarta would accede to Manila's request. He evoked the phrase ASEAN cooperation and brotherhood, the same words he used to ban foreign delegates on the East Timor conference.
